Hi,
I am having trouble producing the correct geojson output. I have a `TrainStation` with a M2M field to `Location` which is a normal pointfield (SRID=4326) which I then serve over DRF.
Before you ask why I use M2M field for location, it is because there are several locations at a station which can be interesting for a user. :-)
I am also using the latest version `0.11.2` at the time of writing.

### models.py
```
class Location(models.Model):

    point = models.PointField()
    last_modified = models.DateTimeField(auto_now=True)
    objects = models.GeoManager()

    class Meta:
        verbose_name = "Location"
        verbose_name_plural = "Locations"
        ordering = ['point']

    def __str__(self):
        return "{}".format(self.point)

class TrainStation(models.Model):

    location_signature = models.CharField(primary_key=True, max_length=32)
    advertised_location_name = models.CharField(max_length=32)
    country_code = models.ForeignKey(Country)
    county_no = models.ForeignKey(County)
    location = models.ManyToManyField(Location)

    def __str__(self):
        return "{}".format(self.location_signature)

```

### serializers.py
```
class LocationSerializer(ModelSerializer):
    
    class Meta:
        model = Location
        fields = [
            'point',
        ]


class FeatureSerializer(GeoFeatureModelSerializer):

    location_signature = PrimaryKeyRelatedField(read_only=True)
    location = LocationSerializer(many=True)

    class Meta:
        model = TrainStation
        geo_field = 'location'
        fields = [
            'location_signature',
            'advertised_location_name',
            'country_code',
            'county_no',
        ]
```

